args.canonical_rel_desc: Indicates that a life cycle or developmental process includes the given stage as one of its distinct component phases.
args.justification: This relation has the same semantics as the other three (a life cycle including a specific stage) but uses a different canonical_rel_name ('has_stage'). Normalizing it to 'includes_life_cycle_stage' with the same description ensures a consistent predicate for all butterfly life-cycle stage composition relations.
